Package edu.ncsu.csc316.dsa.priority_queue

Class AbstractPriorityQueue<K extends Comparable<K>,V>

java.lang.Object
edu.ncsu.csc316.dsa.priority_queue.AbstractPriorityQueue<K,V>
Type Parameters:
K - the type of keys (priorities) stored in the priority queue
V - the type of values that are associated with keys in the priority queue
All Implemented Interfaces:
PriorityQueue<K,V>
Direct Known Subclasses:
HeapPriorityQueue
public abstract class AbstractPriorityQueue<K extends Comparable<K>,V> extends Object implements PriorityQueue<K,V>
A skeletal implementation of the Priority Queue abstract data type. This class provides implementation for common methods that can be implemented the same no matter what specific type of concrete data structure is used to implement the priority queue abstract data type.
Author:
Dr. King

  • Method Details

    • compare

      public int compare(K key1, K key2)
      Compare keys (priorities) to determine their relative ordering. Return a negative number to indicate key1 should appear before key2. Return a positive number to indicate key1 should appear after key2. Return 0 to indicate key1 and key2 are considered equal.
      Parameters:
      key1 - a key to compare
      key2 - a key to compare
      Returns:
      a number to indicate the relative ordering of key1 and key2: a negative number indicates key1 should appear before key2; a positive number indicates key1 should appear after key2; 0 indicates the two keys are considered equal
